The two, and another woman, allegedly entered the home of a 66-year-old Roshnee, Vereeniging, woman yesterday afternoon.They overpowered the woman and dragged her into a bedroom - and allegedly shot her three times when security guards cornered them.The guards were called when neighbours heard the homeowner screaming for help.Police said that a woman was arrested as she tried to flee the scene.Gauteng police spokesman Colonel Lungelo Dlamini said security guards recovered cash from the fleeing woman."While [the homeowner] was being held up the security guards were called."As the guards surrounded the house, the gunman shot the woman - one of his accomplices - and himself."He said that police recovered a pistol from the house.